<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Your Fat Loss Playbook</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:wght@400;600;700;900&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500&family=DM+Mono:wght@300;400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root {
    --bg: #faf8f5;
    --white: #ffffff;
    --ink: #1c1c1c;
    --mid: #555;
    --dim: #999;
    --rule: #e8e4de;
    --orange: #c0440a;
    --orange-light: #fff4ee;
    --orange-mid: rgba(192,68,10,0.1);
    --slate: #2a3f5f;
    --slate-light: #eef2f8;
    --teal: #0f6b5e;
    --teal-light: #edf7f5;
  }

  * { margin:0; padding:0; box-sizing:border-box; }

  body {
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .cover {
    background: #1c1c1c;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 80px 40px 64px;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .cover::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0;
    background: repeating-linear-gradient(
      90deg,
      rgba(255,255,255,0.015) 0px,
      rgba(255,255,255,0.015) 1px,
      transparent 1px,
      transparent 60px
    );
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .cover-tag {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--orange);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .cover h1 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: clamp(40px, 7vw, 80px);
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 1.0;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  .cover h1 em {
    font-style: normal;
    color: var(--orange);
  }

  .cover-sub {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);
    max-width: 480px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }

  .cover-pills { display: flex; gap: 10px; flex-wrap: wrap; }

  .cpill {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 6px 14px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.15);
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75);
  }

  nav {
    background: var(--white);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    padding: 0 40px;
    display: flex;
    overflow-x: auto;
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 100;
  }

  .ntab {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--dim);
    padding: 16px 20px;
    cursor: pointer;
    border: none;
    background: none;
    border-bottom: 2px solid transparent;
    white-space: nowrap;
    transition: all 0.15s;
  }
  .ntab:hover { color: var(--ink); }
  .ntab.active { color: var(--orange); border-bottom-color: var(--orange); }

  .panel { display: none; padding: 48px 40px; max-width: 860px; }
  .panel.active { display: block; }

  .ph {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 34px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  .ps {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 2.5px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--dim);
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }

  .sh2 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
    margin-top: 36px;
  }

  .box {
    padding: 22px 26px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--orange);
    background: var(--orange-light);
  }
  .box.slate { border-left-color: var(--slate); background: var(--slate-light); }
  .box.teal { border-left-color: var(--teal); background: var(--teal-light); }

  .box-label {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--orange);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .box.slate .box-label { color: var(--slate); }
  .box.teal .box-label { color: var(--teal); }

  .box-text { font-size: 14px; color: var(--ink); line-height: 1.75; }

  .week-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(160px, 1fr));
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--rule);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }

  .wcard { background: var(--white); padding: 22px 20px; }
  .wnum { font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-size: 40px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--rule); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .wfocus { font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 2px; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--orange); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .wtext { font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--mid); line-height: 1.65; }

  .ex-wrap { background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--rule); margin-bottom: 28px; }

  .ex-header {
    padding: 16px 20px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .ex-day { font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; }
  .ex-focus { font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 2px; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--orange); margin-top: 3px; }
  .ex-time { font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; color: var(--dim); }

  .block-row {
    padding: 10px 20px;
    background: var(--bg);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--slate);
  }

  table.et { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 13px; }
  table.et th { font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 1.5px; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--dim); padding: 12px 20px; text-align: left; background: var(--bg); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); font-weight: 400; }
  table.et td { padding: 13px 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #f0ece5; color: var(--mid); vertical-align: top; }
  table.et tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  table.et tr:hover td { background: var(--bg); }
  .ename { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 500; margin-bottom: 3px; }
  .enote { font-size: 11.5px; color: var(--dim); font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; line-height: 1.5; }
  .sets { font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 12px; color: var(--orange); white-space: nowrap; }

  .clist { background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--rule); margin-bottom: 28px; }
  .clist-h { padding: 14px 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 2.5px; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--dim); }

  .ci { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 14px; padding: 13px 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #f5f2ed; cursor: pointer; transition: background 0.12s; }
  .ci:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .ci:hover { background: var(--bg); }
  .cb { width: 17px; height: 17px; border: 1.5px solid #ccc; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; transition: all 0.15s; }
  .ci.done .cb { background: var(--teal); border-color: var(--teal); }
  .ci.done .cb::after { content: '✓'; font-size: 10px; color: #fff; font-weight: 700; }
  .ct { font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--ink); }
  .ci.done .ct { color: var(--dim); text-decoration: line-through; }
  .cn { font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; color: var(--dim); margin-top: 3px; }

  .macro-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 1px; background: var(--rule); border: 1px solid var(--rule); margin-bottom: 28px; }
  .mc { background: var(--white); padding: 24px 16px; text-align: center; }
  .mn { font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-size: 30px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--orange); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .mu { font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 9px; color: var(--dim); letter-spacing: 1px; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .ml { font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 1.5px; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--mid); }

  .phase-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1px; background: var(--rule); border: 1px solid var(--rule); margin-bottom: 28px; }
  .phase-card { background: var(--white); padding: 24px 20px; }
  .phase-num { font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 2px; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--orange); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .phase-title { font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-size: 17px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .phase-text { font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--mid); line-height: 1.65; }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .cover, .panel { padding: 40px 20px; }
    nav { padding: 0 8px; }
    .ntab { padding: 14px 12px; }
    .macro-row, .phase-row { grid-template-columns: repeat(2,1fr); }
    .ex-header { flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; align-items: flex-start; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="cover">
  <div class="cover-tag">Your Personal Playbook</div>
  <h1>Lose the Fat.<br>Keep the <em>Muscle.</em></h1>
  <p class="cover-sub">A no-nonsense 12-week guide to dropping body fat and building a leaner, stronger body — without living in the gym or eating like a rabbit.</p>
  <div class="cover-pills">
    <span class="cpill">4 Days / Week</span>
    <span class="cpill">Full Gym</span>
    <span class="cpill">12-Week Program</span>
    <span class="cpill">Fat Loss & Recomp</span>
  </div>
</div>

<nav>
  <button class="ntab active" onclick="show('start')">Getting Started</button>
  <button class="ntab" onclick="show('workouts')">Your Workouts</button>
  <button class="ntab" onclick="show('nutrition')">Nutrition</button>
  <button class="ntab" onclick="show('tracking')">Tracking Progress</button>
  <button class="ntab" onclick="show('faqs')">FAQs</button>
</nav>

<!-- GETTING STARTED -->
<div class="panel active" id="panel-start">
  <div class="ph">Let's get to work.</div>
  <div class="ps">Read this before your first session</div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-label">How This Works</div>
    <div class="box-text">Fat loss comes from your nutrition. Training's job is to preserve and build muscle while you lose fat — so that what's left when the fat comes off looks the way you want it to. You'll train 4 days a week, eat in a moderate calorie deficit with high protein, and check in with your coach weekly. That's the whole system.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="sh2">The three rules.</div>
  <div class="ps" style="margin-top:4px;">Everything else is secondary</div>

  <div class="box teal">
    <div class="box-label">Rule 1</div>
    <div class="box-text"><strong>Hit your protein target every day.</strong> This is the single most important thing you can do. High protein keeps you full, preserves muscle while you're in a calorie deficit, and speeds up your metabolism. Without it, you'll lose muscle alongside fat and end up smaller but not better.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="box slate">
    <div class="box-label">Rule 2</div>
    <div class="box-text"><strong>Show up for your 4 sessions every week.</strong> Missing one session occasionally is fine. Missing them consistently kills results. Block your training days in your calendar like they're appointments you can't cancel. Consistency over 12 weeks beats intensity in any single session.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-label">Rule 3</div>
    <div class="box-text"><strong>Fill in your weekly check-in every Sunday.</strong> This is how your coach adjusts the plan as you progress. A check-in takes 5 minutes and ensures your program stays calibrated to your actual results — not a generic template.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="sh2">Your 4-day schedule.</div>
  <div class="week-grid">
    <div class="wcard"><div class="wnum">MON</div><div class="wfocus">Day A · Lower Body</div><div class="wtext">Squat-focused. Legs and glutes.</div></div>
    <div class="wcard"><div class="wnum">TUE</div><div class="wfocus">Day B · Upper Body</div><div class="wtext">Chest, back, shoulders, arms.</div></div>
    <div class="wcard"><div class="wnum">WED</div><div class="wfocus">Rest Day</div><div class="wtext">Walk 20–30 min. Light activity only.</div></div>
    <div class="wcard"><div class="wnum">THU</div><div class="wfocus">Day C · Lower Body</div><div class="wtext">Deadlift-focused. Hamstrings and glutes.</div></div>
    <div class="wcard"><div class="wnum">FRI</div><div class="wfocus">Day D · Upper Body</div><div class="wtext">Push and pull with a finisher.</div></div>
    <div class="wcard"><div class="wnum">SAT/SUN</div><div class="wfocus">Rest</div><div class="wtext">Walking is great. Nothing intense.</div></div>
  </div>

  <div class="sh2">Before your first session.</div>
  <div class="clist">
    <div class="clist-h">Checklist — Complete Before Day 1</div>
    <div class="ci" onclick="tog(this)"><div class="cb"></div><div><div class="ct">Take baseline photos — front and side in fitted clothing</div><div class="cn">The most important thing you'll do today</div></div></div>
    <div class="ci" onclick="tog(this)"><div class="cb"></div><div><div class="ct">Weigh yourself first thing in the morning (before eating or drinking)</div></div></div>
    <div class="ci" onclick="tog(this)"><div class="cb"></div><div><div class="ct">Measure your waist at your belly button and hips at the widest point</div></div></div>
    <div class="ci" onclick="tog(this)"><div class="cb"></div><div><div class="ct">Download MyFitnessPal and log what you eat for 3 days before changing anything</div><div class="cn">Awareness before action</div></div></div>
    <div class="ci" onclick="tog(this)"><div class="cb"></div><div><div class="ct">Block all 4 training days in your calendar this week</div></div></div>
    <div class="ci" onclick="tog(this)"><div class="cb"></div><div><div class="ct">Read through your first workout so there are no surprises in the gym</div></div></div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- WORKOUTS -->
<div class="panel" id="panel-workouts">
  <div class="ph">Your Workouts.</div>
  <div class="ps">4 sessions per week — upper/lower split</div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-label">How to Use These Workouts</div>
    <div class="box-text">Pick a weight that feels challenging by the last 2–3 reps of each set — hard but not impossible. Write down what you lifted. Every session, try to do one more rep or add a small amount of weight. That's called progressive overload, and it's the reason your body will change.</div>
  </div>

  <!-- DAY A -->
  <div class="ex-wrap">
    <div class="ex-header">
      <div><div class="ex-day">Day A — Monday</div><div class="ex-focus">Lower Body · Squat Focus</div></div>
      <div class="ex-time">~55 minutes</div>
    </div>
    <div class="block-row">Warm-Up · 8 Minutes</div>
    <table class="et">
      <thead><tr><th>Exercise</th><th>Sets × Reps</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Treadmill Walk or Bike</div><div class="enote">Easy pace to raise heart rate</div></td><td class="sets">5 min</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Bodyweight Squat</div><div class="enote">Slow and deliberate. Find your depth.</div></td><td class="sets">2 × 10</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="block-row">Working Sets</div>
    <table class="et">
      <thead><tr><th>Exercise</th><th>Sets × Reps</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Barbell Back Squat</div><div class="enote">Main lift. Feet shoulder-width, chest tall, squat to depth. Rest 2 min between sets.</div></td><td class="sets">4 × 8–10</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Leg Press</div><div class="enote">Feet shoulder-width. Full range. Slow on the way down. Rest 90 sec.</div></td><td class="sets">3 × 12–15</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Dumbbell Walking Lunge</div><div class="enote">Front knee over ankle. Step with control. Rest 60 sec.</div></td><td class="sets">3 × 10 each leg</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Leg Curl Machine</div><div class="enote">3-second lowering phase. Rest 60 sec.</div></td><td class="sets">3 × 12–15</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Metabolic Finisher: Sled Push or Rowing Machine</div><div class="enote">8 minutes. 40 seconds on, 20 seconds off. Burns extra calories without hurting recovery.</div></td><td class="sets">8 min</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- DAY B -->
  <div class="ex-wrap">
    <div class="ex-header">
      <div><div class="ex-day">Day B — Tuesday</div><div class="ex-focus">Upper Body · Push + Pull</div></div>
      <div class="ex-time">~55 minutes</div>
    </div>
    <div class="block-row">Warm-Up · 8 Minutes</div>
    <table class="et">
      <thead><tr><th>Exercise</th><th>Sets × Reps</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Band Pull-Apart</div><div class="enote">Light band. Activates your rear shoulders before pressing.</div></td><td class="sets">2 × 15</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Arm Circles + Shoulder Rolls</div></td><td class="sets">60 seconds</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="block-row">Working Sets</div>
    <table class="et">
      <thead><tr><th>Exercise</th><th>Sets × Reps</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Barbell Bench Press</div><div class="enote">Bar to lower chest. Controlled back up. Rest 2 min.</div></td><td class="sets">4 × 8–10</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Barbell Row</div><div class="enote">Brace your core. Pull elbow straight back. Rest 90 sec.</div></td><td class="sets">4 × 10–12</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Dumbbell Shoulder Press</div><div class="enote">Seated or standing. Full extension overhead. Rest 90 sec.</div></td><td class="sets">3 × 10–12</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Lat Pulldown</div><div class="enote">Pull to upper chest. Squeeze your lats at the bottom. Rest 90 sec.</div></td><td class="sets">3 × 10–12</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Dumbbell Curl + Tricep Pushdown Superset</div><div class="enote">Do both back to back, then rest 60 sec. Efficient arm work.</div></td><td class="sets">3 × 12–15 each</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Metabolic Finisher: Battle Ropes or Jump Rope</div><div class="enote">8 minutes. 30 sec on, 30 sec off.</div></td><td class="sets">8 min</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- DAY C -->
  <div class="ex-wrap">
    <div class="ex-header">
      <div><div class="ex-day">Day C — Thursday</div><div class="ex-focus">Lower Body · Hinge Focus</div></div>
      <div class="ex-time">~55 minutes</div>
    </div>
    <div class="block-row">Warm-Up · 8 Minutes</div>
    <table class="et">
      <thead><tr><th>Exercise</th><th>Sets × Reps</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Hip Hinge Pattern with Broomstick</div><div class="enote">Practice before loading. Flat back, hinge at hips.</div></td><td class="sets">2 × 10</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Glute Bridge</div><div class="enote">Squeeze hard at the top. 2-second hold.</div></td><td class="sets">2 × 12</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="block-row">Working Sets</div>
    <table class="et">
      <thead><tr><th>Exercise</th><th>Sets × Reps</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Romanian Deadlift</div><div class="enote">Main lift today. Hinge at hips, feel the stretch. Rest 2 min.</div></td><td class="sets">4 × 10–12</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Bulgarian Split Squat</div><div class="enote">Back foot on bench. Front leg does the work. Go slow. Rest 90 sec each leg.</div></td><td class="sets">3 × 10 each leg</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Leg Curl Machine</div><div class="enote">Slow and controlled. Rest 60 sec.</div></td><td class="sets">3 × 12–15</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Hip Thrust (Barbell or Dumbbell)</div><div class="enote">Upper back on bench. Drive hips up. Glute squeeze at top. Rest 90 sec.</div></td><td class="sets">3 × 12–15</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Metabolic Finisher: Stairmaster or Incline Treadmill Walk</div><div class="enote">12 minutes at a challenging pace. Burns calories, doesn't hurt legs for Friday.</div></td><td class="sets">12 min</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- DAY D -->
  <div class="ex-wrap">
    <div class="ex-header">
      <div><div class="ex-day">Day D — Friday</div><div class="ex-focus">Upper Body + Full Body Finisher</div></div>
      <div class="ex-time">~60 minutes</div>
    </div>
    <div class="block-row">Warm-Up · 8 Minutes</div>
    <table class="et">
      <thead><tr><th>Exercise</th><th>Sets × Reps</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Band Pull-Apart + Face Pull</div><div class="enote">Shoulder health before a pressing session</div></td><td class="sets">2 × 15 each</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="block-row">Working Sets</div>
    <table class="et">
      <thead><tr><th>Exercise</th><th>Sets × Reps</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Incline Dumbbell Press</div><div class="enote">Upper chest focus. Controlled descent. Rest 90 sec.</div></td><td class="sets">4 × 10–12</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Chest-Supported Dumbbell Row</div><div class="enote">Chest on the bench. Full range. Pause at top. Rest 90 sec.</div></td><td class="sets">4 × 10–12</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Cable Lateral Raise</div><div class="enote">Light weight. Lead with elbow. Rest 45 sec.</div></td><td class="sets">3 × 15</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Face Pull</div><div class="enote">Rope to eye level, pull to ears, elbows high. Rest 45 sec.</div></td><td class="sets">3 × 15</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Ab Circuit: Dead Bug + Side Plank + Cable Crunch</div><div class="enote">All three back to back = 1 round. Rest 60 sec between rounds.</div></td><td class="sets">3 rounds</td></tr>
        <tr><td><div class="ename">Metabolic Finisher: Any Cardio Machine</div><div class="enote">10 minutes. Push the pace — this is the end of your training week.</div></td><td class="sets">10 min</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- NUTRITION -->
<div class="panel" id="panel-nutrition">
  <div class="ph">Nutrition.</div>
  <div class="ps">2,200 calories · protein first · every day</div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-label">The Truth About Fat Loss</div>
    <div class="box-text">Fat loss is 80% what you eat. Training builds the muscle and raises your metabolism — but you cannot out-train a poor diet. 2,200 calories puts you in a real but sustainable deficit. High protein keeps you full, preserves your muscle, and speeds up your metabolism. No banned foods, no crash dieting. Just consistent eating within your targets.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="sh2">Your daily targets.</div>
  <div class="macro-row">
    <div class="mc"><div class="mn">2,200</div><div class="mu">calories per day</div><div class="ml">Daily Calories</div></div>
    <div class="mc"><div class="mn">180g</div><div class="mu">minimum, every single day</div><div class="ml">Protein — Non-Negotiable</div></div>
    <div class="mc"><div class="mn">55g</div><div class="mu">supports hormones + fullness</div><div class="ml">Fat Minimum</div></div>
    <div class="mc"><div class="mn">~165g</div><div class="mu">fuels training + energy</div><div class="ml">Carbohydrates</div></div>
  </div>

  <div class="box teal">
    <div class="box-label">Why Protein Is the Priority</div>
    <div class="box-text">When you're in a calorie deficit, your body wants to burn muscle for energy alongside fat. High protein intake prevents that. It also keeps you fuller longer — gram for gram, protein is the most satiating macronutrient. Hit 180g protein first every day. The calories and other macros will fall into place around it.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="sh2">How the 2,200 calories break down across 4 meals.</div>
  <div class="ps" style="margin-top:4px;">4 meals per day — timed around your training</div>

