<!-- FAQS -->
<div class="panel" id="panel-faqs">
  <div class="ph">Frequently Asked Questions.</div>
  <div class="ps">Common concerns, honest answers</div>

  <div class="sh2" style="margin-top:0;">"I'm not losing weight. What's wrong?"</div>
  <div class="box" style="margin-top:12px;">
    <div class="box-text">Two most common causes: eating more than you think (liquid calories, portion sizes), or not eating enough protein (which causes muscle loss that masks fat loss on the scale). Track everything honestly for one week and share it with your coach. The answer is almost always in the data.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="sh2">"I'm hungry all the time."</div>
  <div class="box teal" style="margin-top:12px;">
    <div class="box-text">Increase protein and vegetables first — both are very filling per calorie. Also check your sleep. Poor sleep spikes hunger hormones dramatically. If you're sleeping under 6 hours, hunger control becomes nearly impossible regardless of what you eat.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="sh2">"Can I do extra cardio to speed things up?"</div>
  <div class="box slate" style="margin-top:12px;">
    <div class="box-text">You can — but the finishers in your workouts already handle extra calorie burn. If you want to add walking on rest days (20–40 min), that's great and won't hurt recovery. Avoid adding intense cardio sessions on top of your 4 training days — it raises cortisol, hurts recovery, and often makes people hungrier without burning as many extra calories as they think.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="sh2">"I missed two sessions this week. Do I start over?"</div>
  <div class="box" style="margin-top:12px;">
    <div class="box-text">No. Pick up exactly where you left off. Don't try to cram 6 sessions into one week to "make up" for it — that's how people get injured and burnt out. One bad week doesn't erase four good ones. Consistency is measured in months, not days.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="sh2">"When will I see results?"</div>
  <div class="box teal" style="margin-top:12px;">
    <div class="box-text">Most people notice something in weeks 3–4 — clothes fitting differently, energy improving, strength going up. Visible fat loss that others notice usually happens in weeks 6–8. Dramatic before-and-after differences show up at week 12. The timeline is the same for nearly everyone who follows the program consistently. Trust it.</div>
  </div>
</div>

